<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-21-0338 </DOCNO><TEXT>Six legislative actions related to geothermal resources and taken by theState of California in 1985 and 1986 are described. In addition, thestatus of eight bills before the 99th Congress related to geothermalenergy is summarized. The state bills have to do with leases, royalties,revenues, taxes, and geothermal power plant development. Congressionalbills relate to amendments to the Tax Reform Act, control of geothermalenergy, and energy conservation.</TEXT></DOC>